    "48b68ed7-85a6-4ce2-9929-73c9a0f262cb": {
      "id": "48b68ed7-85a6-4ce2-9929-73c9a0f262cb",
      "name": "Method (from the official Pricing & Margin Policy)",
      "content": "- Margin is measured as a **share of the sale price** (true margin), target **20%** — a FLOOR,\n  not a ceiling.\n- Taken over **fully-loaded cost**: AI/vendor fee + payment processing + an allocated share of\n  infrastructure/overhead.\n- Solve backwards for price:  **price = base cost ÷ (1 − margin − payment-fee rate)**.\n- Never below cost. Usage is **metered** (the price buys a bounded allowance), so cost can never\n  run away and every sale is cash-positive from day one.",
      "type": "spreadsheet",
      "parentId": "839a1641-c118-42a0-99b8-bd72c3dc8faa",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "prefix": "",
      "metadata": {
        "createdAt": 1784189072420,
        "updatedAt": 1784189072420
      }
    },
    "677ea8f1-41aa-4c79-8841-5075031bf9c3": {
      "id": "677ea8f1-41aa-4c79-8841-5075031bf9c3",
      "name": "Fully-loaded cost of a Professional member (per month, industry-standard estimates)",
      "content": "| Line item | Est. / mo | Basis (industry standard) |\n|---|---|---|\n| Premium AI outputs (metered allowance): premium podcast/video voices, image generation, cloud LLM for smart features, transcription | ~$12 | Vendors' published pay-as-you-go prices (OpenAI TTS/LLM, image gen, AssemblyAI) × a reasonable monthly allowance |\n| Infrastructure + overhead share (hosting, auth, database, rate-limiting, monitoring, domain) | ~$3 | Typical lean-SaaS per-user cost at modest scale, amortized |\n| **Base fully-loaded cost** | **≈ $15/user/mo** | |\n| Payment fee — web/Mac | ~2.9% + $0.30 | Stripe standard card processing |\n| Payment fee — iPhone/iPad | 15–30% | Apple In-App Purchase (30% standard; **15% Small-Business** rate under $1M/yr) |",
      "type": "note",
      "parentId": "839a1641-c118-42a0-99b8-bd72c3dc8faa",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "prefix": "",
      "metadata": {
        "createdAt": 1784189072420,
        "updatedAt": 1784189072420
      }
    },
    "1227d4db-c672-49a8-996f-63fbdf4f9d31": {
      "id": "1227d4db-c672-49a8-996f-63fbdf4f9d31",
      "name": "Backward calculation → price (20% margin)",
      "content": "- **Web / Mac** (fee ~3%):  $15 ÷ (1 − 0.20 − 0.03) = $15 ÷ 0.77 ≈ **$19.99/mo**\n- **iPhone** (Apple 30%):  $15 ÷ (1 − 0.20 − 0.30) = $15 ÷ 0.50 ≈ **$29.99/mo**\n  - iPhone at Apple's **15% Small-Business** rate: $15 ÷ 0.65 ≈ **$22.99/mo**",
      "type": "note",
      "parentId": "839a1641-c118-42a0-99b8-bd72c3dc8faa",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "prefix": "",
      "metadata": {
        "createdAt": 1784189072420,
        "updatedAt": 1784189072420
      }
    },
    "4d798663-8600-497e-bc45-fa95cee9c6bf": {
      "id": "4d798663-8600-497e-bc45-fa95cee9c6bf",
      "name": "Proposed tiers",
      "content": "| Tier | Web / Mac | iPhone | Includes |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| **Free** | $0 | $0 | Core app forever — outlines, Second Brain, on-device/Gemma AI. Cost to us ≈ $0. |\n| **Professional** | **~$19.99/mo** | ~$29.99/mo | Full premium allowance: cloud AI, video + podcast, all export formats. 20% real margin. |\n| **Student** | **~$9.99/mo** | ~$14.99/mo | Same tool, a **lighter premium allowance** so the discount stays cash-positive (students use less). Verified with a .edu email. |\n\n**Student guardrail:** a true half-price student discount only stays profitable if it comes with\na **smaller premium quota** — otherwise the discounted price would dip below cost and we'd be\nfronting money (violates \"never front money\"). So students get the same *tool*, a smaller monthly\n*quota* of the expensive outputs.",
      "type": "note",
      "parentId": "839a1641-c118-42a0-99b8-bd72c3dc8faa",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "prefix": "",
      "metadata": {
        "createdAt": 1784189072420,
        "updatedAt": 1784189072420
      }
    },
    "af8e0118-36ab-443f-9e1a-c64c7afb7c0c": {
      "id": "af8e0118-36ab-443f-9e1a-c64c7afb7c0c",
      "name": "The value anchor (Howard, 2026-07-16) — this is a headline, not a footnote",
      "content": "Paid access to **any** serious LLM is a **$20/month floor** — ChatGPT Plus, Claude Pro, and\nGemini Advanced are all exactly $20/mo. So IdiamPro Professional at ~$19.99 means the customer\npays the price of **one bare chatbot** and gets the **entire thinking system** on top of it\n(outlining, consolidation, Second Brain, and every finished output — video, podcast, docs, sites,\n21 languages). Great deal for them; cash-positive for us. Use this comparison prominently in the\npricing copy.",
      "type": "note",
      "parentId": "839a1641-c118-42a0-99b8-bd72c3dc8faa",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "prefix": "",
      "metadata": {
        "createdAt": 1784189072420,
        "updatedAt": 1784189072420
      }
    },
    "29465137-c299-443c-a221-a7e1180e8dd6": {
      "id": "29465137-c299-443c-a221-a7e1180e8dd6",
      "name": "Assumptions to confirm (the levers that move the numbers)",
      "content": "1. **The premium allowance per tier** — the single biggest cost driver, and really a product call.\n2. The **~$3/user overhead** estimate.\n3. **Per-platform pricing** (web cheaper, iPhone higher for Apple's cut) vs. **one blended price**.",
      "type": "note",
      "parentId": "839a1641-c118-42a0-99b8-bd72c3dc8faa",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "prefix": "",
      "metadata": {
        "createdAt": 1784189072420,
        "updatedAt": 1784189072420
      }
    },
    "8d4b224b-b6a6-4e22-ae49-be7ddcaa1943": {
      "id": "8d4b224b-b6a6-4e22-ae49-be7ddcaa1943",
      "name": "Optional enhancements / add-on revenue lines (to fold into the model)",
      "content": "Each stays priced at the same 20%-margin-over-cost discipline, so every one is cash-positive:\n\n1. **Overage top-up packs** — when a member exhausts their monthly premium allowance, they buy a\n   pack (e.g. +5 videos, +10 podcasts) at the same per-unit margin rather than being cut off.\n   Keeps heavy users cash-positive instead of either losing them or eating a loss.\n2. **Premium-voice upgrade** — studio-grade voices (e.g. ElevenLabs-tier) as a paid step up from\n   the standard cloud voices; higher cost → higher price, same margin.\n3. **BYOK discount path** — a member who brings their own API key covers their own AI cost, so\n   they pay a lower base price (near just the overhead + margin). Already in the monetization model.\n4. **Annual billing** — offer annual at ~2 months free vs monthly; standard SaaS lever that\n   improves cash flow and retention without touching the per-unit margin.\n5. **(Future) Team / seat licensing** — belongs to IdiamTeam, out of scope for this launch model.",
      "type": "note",
      "parentId": "839a1641-c118-42a0-99b8-bd72c3dc8faa",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "prefix": "",
      "metadata": {
        "createdAt": 1784189072420,
        "updatedAt": 1784189072420
      }
    },
    "0bcaece2-0a5c-4197-8bf8-e8faf40802b4": {
      "id": "0bcaece2-0a5c-4197-8bf8-e8faf40802b4",
      "name": "Guardrails carried from policy / monetization model",
      "content": "- Core app (outlines + everyday text AI on free/on-device Gemma) is **free forever** — only the\n  premium OUTPUTS are paywalled (free-tier-never-useless honored).\n- **First-month free trial** of premium features on the free on-device voice (zero cost to us).\n- iOS routes through **Apple IAP** (compliance-first) via RevenueCat; web/Mac may use own processor.\n- Phone-verify anti-farming; server-side metered lock enforces the allowance.\n\n---\n*This is a working analysis for planning, not a final price sheet or financial advice. Lock the\nreal numbers once the funded company account exists and true vendor costs + Apple's exact cut are\nknown. See memory: project-pricing-margin-policy, project-monetization-model.*",
      "type": "note",
      "parentId": "839a1641-c118-42a0-99b8-bd72c3dc8faa",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "prefix": "",
      "metadata": {
        "createdAt": 1784189072420,
        "updatedAt": 1784189072420
      }
    }
  },
